Come and join a dynamic and challenging team within the Intel Data Platform Group, focused on defining developing and deploying the engineering infrastructure, to support the development of the next generation Intel Server Platforms. This position is to engage and collaborate with upstream partners such platform validation and infrastructure architects, and turn their usage models and requirements into world class Cluster SW stack and services solutions, to enable high and medium density infrastructure Invent design build deliver solutions that drive standards, and efficiency across the ecosystem, that allows platform development and validation engineers to quickly deploy run and scale their solutions. Join us and contribute to a worldwide organization that develops the products and technologies, that power nine of every 10 servers sold worldwide. 
The ideal candidate should exhibit the following behavioral traits: 
Highly motivated individual willing to work under pressure and deliver high quality results on time 
Strong quantitative, analytical skills to debug and isolate problems 
Problem solving and conflict resolution skills 
Effective prioritization and time management skills 
Stakeholder management, strong collaboration, tolerance for ambiguity and critical thinking 
Excellent teamwork ethics 
Willing to work in an agile work environment with a fast-paced task flow 
Passion for quality and relentless improvement want to stand out 
Qualifications 
Candidate must possess the below minimum qualifications to be initially considered for this position. This is an entry level position and will be compensated accordingly. 
Minimum Qualifications 
Candidate must have BS or MS degree in Software Engineering, Computer Science or related field. 
Minimum of 1 year of experience in: 
Proficiency in Linux environment 
Programming proficiency in relevant software and or scripting languages Python bash shell 
Know how on low level hardware programming (RS232C, Ethernet networking, IP networking, USB, SPI flashing, dediprog etc.) 
Preferred qualifications 
Minimum of 1 year of experience in any of the following: 
Deploying and debugging Baremetal system provisioning with OpenStack Ironic IPMI Redfish PXEiPXE 
Git source control management gitlab github gerrit etc. 
Intel Architecture and Enterprise Server system technologies and architecture 
Infrastructure automation tooling Ansible Jenkins 
Datacenter Cloud HW and infrastructure 
Developing and deploying Cluster and Datacenter Cloud solutions, Kubernetes Docker OpenStack 
Developing Telemetry solutions Elastic, ELK, Prometheus, Kafka, Grafana 
Sphinx rest documentation system 
Good understanding and experience good development practices like Scrum Agile coding standards etc. 
Tolerance of ambiguity highly effective in ambiguous environment and demonstrated experience to develop clear strategies and plans with appropriately managed risks 
Communication proficiency in facilitating clear and consistent understanding across time zones and language boundaries 
Inside this Business Group 
The Data Platforms Engineering and Architecture (DPEA) Group invents, designs & builds the world's most critical computing platforms which fuel Intel's most important business and solve the world's most fundamental problems. DPEA enables that data center which is the underpinning for every data-driven service, from artificial intelligence to 5G to high-performance computing, and DCG delivers the products and technologies—spanning software, processors, storage, I/O, and networking solutions—that fuel cloud, communications, enterprise, and government data centers around the world. 
Other Locations 
 
Virtual US and Canada 
